text.section:
No permit to construct or expand a municipal solid waste disposal facility shall be approved unless the applicant affirmatively demonstrates and the cabinet makes a written finding in the preliminary determination made pursuant to KRS 224.40-310(2) that the application conforms to and is consistent with all of the following:
The capacity needs identified in the area solid waste management plan;
Other elements of the area solid waste management plan, for permit applications filed after approval of those elements;
The statewide solid waste reduction and management plan, for permit applications filed after completion of the plan; and
Applicable zoning regulations adopted pursuant to KRS Chapter 100.
